 {"id":"frankenredis-wgxf","title":"CONFORMANCE: redis expiry parity matrix","description":"Wire core_expiry.json via live_redis_diff. EXPIRE/PEXPIRE/EXPIREAT/PEXPIREAT/TTL/PTTL/EXPIRETIME/PEXPIRETIME/PERSIST.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-24T12:41:46.677424333Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T13:16:19.496497000Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"closed_at":"2026-04-24T13:16:19.496497000Z","close_reason":"Skipped as test-harness limitation: the 256-case core_expiry fixture pins now_ms and queries absolute-time TTL at millisecond granularity, but upstream reads wall-clock; every case cascades into a fixture-clock-vs-wall-clock divergence. Needs upstream TIME override or fixture-clock rewrite — tracked on shared 7rp6 + the skip message inside the test function."}
