 {"id":"frankenredis-faqe","title":"[HIGH] ACL parity: 31 divergences — AUTH default-user password flow, ACL CAT wording + order, ACL DRYRUN reply shape, ACL SAVE/LOAD config-file awareness, ACL LOG entries","description":"Surfaced by live_redis_core_acl_matches_runtime (31 cases): (a) AUTH rejects SETUSER-configured passwords because fr-runtime's default ACL state is nopass-locked; every auth_* + acl_*_auth_* + acl_*_reauth_* case sees 'ERR AUTH <password> called without any password configured' instead of matching upstream. (b) ACL LIST default-user rule order: ours emits 'user default on sanitize-payload nopass ~* &* +@all' vs upstream 'user default on nopass sanitize-payload ~* &* +@all' — different flag ordering. (c) ACL CAT unknown-category wording: ours 'ERR Unknown ACL cat category' vs upstream 'ERR Unknown category'. (d) ACL CAT <category> entry order: our command-to-category mapping iterates in registration order, upstream in dict order. (e) ACL SAVE/LOAD returns OK where upstream returns 'ERR This Redis instance is not configured to use an ACL file' (our harness spawns without an ACL file too but fr-runtime still pretends SAVE succeeded). (f) ACL DRYRUN returns Error where upstream returns BulkString with the denial message. (g) ACL LOG is empty (we don't record failed auth attempts) where upstream has 3 entries. (h) ACL GENPASS extra-args emits 'wrong number of arguments for acl|genpass' vs upstream 'ERR unknown subcommand or wrong number of arguments for GENPASS'. Fix in fr-runtime + fr-command ACL paths.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T13:14:56.156122998Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T13:14:56.156122998Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
