+{"id":"frankenredis-1pe7","title":"[HIGH] DEBUG DIGEST/DIGEST-VALUE/OBJECT parity — 48 divergences across digest-computation + DEBUG OBJECT encoding/addr/serialize fields","description":"Surfaced by live_redis_core_debug_matches_runtime (48 cases after enable-debug-command yes): (a) DEBUG DIGEST / DIGEST-VALUE — fr-runtime doesn't implement the xor-SHA1-of-per-key-digest algorithm upstream uses, so every digest case diverges. (b) DEBUG OBJECT — upstream reply is 'Value at:0x... refcount:1 encoding:<enc> serializedlength:N lru:... lru_seconds_idle:N type:<type>'; ours emits a shorter 'refcount:1 encoding:<enc>' without the pointer/lru/serialized fields. (c) DEBUG SET-ACTIVE-EXPIRE invalid-value / wrong-arity wording differs. (d) Case-insensitive DEBUG subcommand dispatch — upstream normalises, ours may not. Fix: wire DEBUG DIGEST / DIGEST-VALUE in fr-runtime + fill in the full DEBUG OBJECT reply + align SET-ACTIVE-EXPIRE error wording + lowercase dispatch.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T13:25:45.276247292Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T13:25:45.276247292Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
